  <refnamediv>
    <refname>multithresh</refname>
    <refpurpose>This function is used to get multilevel image thresholds using Otsu's method.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   B = multithres(A,thresh)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>A:</term>
      <listitem><para> image matrix of the source image.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>B :</term>
      <listitem><para> Set of threshold values used to quantize an image, returned as a 1-by-N vector, whose data type is the same as image A.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>thresh :</term>
      <listitem><para> Number of threshold values, specified as a positive integer scalar value.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
thresh = multithresh(A,thresh) returns thresh a 1-by-thresh vector containing N threshold values using Otsu's method..
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
i = imread("lena.jpeg",0);
m = multithresh(i,67);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>
</refentry>
